description: This file defines two public classes, 'Lesson' and 'LeaderboardEntry', which are likely part of the data models for a learning or training feature in the application. The 'Lesson' class includes properties related to educational content, while 'LeaderboardEntry' pertains to user rankings based on scores.

classes.name: Lesson
classes.description: Represents a learning module with properties such as id, title, summary, estimated minutes, and premium access status.

classes.name: LeaderboardEntry
classes.description: Represents a user's position on a leaderboard with properties for display name and score.

methods.name: Lesson.mock
methods.description: Factory constructor to create a mock or sample Lesson instance with provided id and title, optional premium flag, and default summary and duration.

methods.name: LeaderboardEntry.mock
methods.description: Factory constructor to create a mock or sample LeaderboardEntry with specified user and score.
